class Solution {
    public List<Integer> grayCode(int n) {
        List<Integer> res = new ArrayList<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < (1 << n); i++) {
            res.add(i ^ (i >> 1));
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(2^n)
space complexity: O(2^n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses the mathematical property that the i-th Gray code is i XOR (i >> 1). Generates the sequence in a single pass with minimal CPU instructions and no recursion, yielding optimal speed and low energy usage.

